    {
      "block_type": "procedure",
      "id": "cylinder_head_installation_contd",
      "title": "Installation (Cont'd)",
      "steps": [
        {
          "step": 7,
          "text": "Install camshaft and camshaft brackets. Tighten camshaft bracket bolts gradually in three stages: (a) 2 N\u00b7m (0.2 kg-m, 1.4 ft-lb) (b) 6 N\u00b7m (0.6 kg-m, 4.3 ft-lb) (c) 9 - 11.8 N\u00b7m (0.92 - 1.20 kg-m, 6.7 - 8.7 ft-lb)",
          "figure_ref": "fig1",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": [
            "If any part of valve assembly or camshaft is replaced, check valve clearance according to the reference data. After completing assembly, check valve clearance. Refer to 'Checking' and 'Adjusting' in 'VALVE CLEARANCE'.",
            "Reference data for initial setting of valve clearance (Cold): Intake 0.30 mm (0.012 in), Exhaust 0.35 mm (0.014 in)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "step": 8,
          "text": "Assemble camshaft sprocket with chain. Set timing chain by aligning mating marks with those of camshaft sprockets. Make sure sprocket's mating marks face engine front.",
          "figure_ref": "fig2",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 9,
          "text": "Install camshaft sprocket bolts. Make sure camshafts are aligned as shown in figure.",
          "figure_ref": "fig3",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        }
      ]
    },
